Subject:   set_level() in monster.c
Author:    Vertebraker
Level:     Administrator
Message: 
 
monster.c now has the capability of automatically setting 
wc/ac/hp of a monster to the levels specified in monster.guide 
 
simply set_level(20); and it will set the wc/ac/hp of the monster 
to the numbers specified in monster.guide 
 
or set_level(4); 
  set_level(25); <- any number specified by the monster.guide 
 
if your monster is out of the ranges in monster.guide you must 
specify the values themselves 
 
if you want greater or lesser parameters for these functions 
you must specify them yourself after the set_level() call. 
